          "c. E(X) = ∫∫(x * 4x^2y)dydx = ∫(2x^3)dx = 1/2 * x^4 |^1_0 = 1/2 = 0.5 => E(X) = 0.5",
          "d. E(Y) = ∫∫(y * 4x^2y)dydx = ∫(4/3 * x^3)dx = 1/3 * x^4 |^1_0 = 1/3 => E(Y) = 1/3",
          "e. E(XY) = ∫∫(xy * 4x^2y)dydx = ∫(4/3 * x^4)dx = 1/5 * x^5 |^1_0 = 1/5 => E(XY) = 1/5",
